Hi Nicole Tv I noticed that you use auto-generated captions on your videos. Unfortunately, auto-generated captions contain tons of mistakes that make it harder for the 360 million folks globally who rely on closed captions to understand your videos! For example, when you are in the bathroom getting ready and y'all are talking about the PlayStation your husband said "I don't want to bring this" but the caption said, "I'm going to write this." Mistakes like this make it harder for people with hearing impairments to fully enjoy your videos. I know I really enjoy seeing the content you make and want other people to be able to enjoy it too. Itâ€™s really easy to add your own captions to videos either through Youtube or through other platforms, like CADET and Amara. I hope you take this into consideration and make your videos more accessible!

The sensation of giving birth is really something else. Without being induced (which is pretty much pain in a drip) you can handle labor pain but that induced pain hits different. Waves of pain just wash over you. Your whole body lights up with it and you have to be quiet and get through it. Thats without epidural. You can do it if you don't panic and all other factors health wise are in your favor. You pray. Stay calm. Listen to the nurses. Listen to your body. You'll be fine.
